snippet.title: International Superstar Soccer 2000 aka ISS (Brazil x England Gameplay) Playstation
snippet.description:
Subscribe! https://goo.gl/HlVgzD Favorite and like! :D


International Superstar Soccer is the name of a series of football (soccer) video games developed by Japanese company Konami, mostly by their Osaka branch, Konami Computer Entertainment Osaka. It should not be confused with KCET's Pro Evolution Soccer series (also known as Winning Eleven), which was originally developed for the PlayStation. ISS 2000 was also released for the Nintendo 64 console.

As usual, you can play in a range of game modes, from 4 player exhibition, training, vs, World League against every team in the world, and a collection of scenario games that have you completing certain elements of a game in order to complete it. - PlayStation DataCenter
